Find gene symbols using the alias2Symbol function from limma.

a2s = rep(NA, length(assayed_genes))
for(i in 1:length(assayed_genes)){
  gi = assayed_genes[i]
  ai = alias2Symbol(gi)
  if(length(ai) > 1){
    print(gi)
    print(ai)
  }
  a2s[i] = ai[1]
}

Check gene expression for each gene set

dim(gene_info)
## [1] 2000    3
for(k in 1:length(gene_sets)){
  if(length(gene_sets[[k]]) < 10) { next }
  
  print(k)
  set_k = paste0("set_", k)
  print(gene_sets[[k]])
  
  genes = gene_info[sym_in_data %in% gene_sets[[k]], gene_symbol]

  n_genes = sum(genes %in% ct$`Gene name`)
  print(sprintf("found %d genes.", n_genes))

  if(n_genes == 0) { next }

  df = ct[`Gene name` %in% genes,]
  dim(df)
  df[1:2,]
  
  stopifnot(all(str_to_lower(df$`Cell type`) %in% 
                  str_to_lower(cell_group$Cell_type)))
  
  mat1 = match(str_to_lower(df$`Cell type`), 
               str_to_lower(cell_group$Cell_type))
  
  df = cbind(df, cell_group[mat1,])
  df[1:2,]
  
  df$Cell_type = factor(df$Cell_type, levels = cell_group$Cell_type)
  df$Cell_group = factor(df$Cell_group, 
                         levels = unique(cell_group$Cell_group))
  
  p1 = ggplot(df, aes(x=Cell_type, y=log10(nTPM + 0.1), fill=Cell_group)) + 
    geom_boxplot() + xlab("Cell type") + ggtitle(set_k) + 
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) + 
    scale_fill_brewer(palette="RdBu")

  print(p1)
}
